## June 3 2026 — v0.4.0
- Remove backtracking support, add `peek` parser combinator for lookaheads.

## June 2 2026 — v0.3.1
- Fix: Markdown parser now parses markdown if headers don't have a blank line after them.

## May 28 2026 — v0.3.0
- New: `tarsec/parsers/markdown` subpath export — a CommonMark-ish markdown parser built entirely from Tarsec combinators, with ATX/setext headings, lists (incl. GFM `- [ ]` task items), tables, block quotes, autolinks (angled and bare-URL), inline HTML (open/close/self-closing tags and comments), HTML entity decoding, reference-style links / footnotes, frontmatter, and a nested-inline AST that round-trips constructs like ``**[link](u)**`` and ``*a `code` b*``.

## Apr 15 2026 — v0.2.2
- `quotedString` now allows backslash-escaping the inner quote — e.g. `"a \"b\" c"` parses as one quoted string of length 9.

## Apr 13 2026 — v0.2.1
- `quote` / `quotedString` accept backticks in addition to `'` and `"`, and the closing quote must match the opener (so a single-quoted string can freely contain `"` and backticks, etc.).

## Apr 2 2026 — v0.2.0
- Better parse-error reporting via rightmost-failure tracking — diagnostics surface the deepest failure across alternatives, with line/column info and a pretty rendered message.

## v0.0.19
- adds `captureCaptures`
